&lt;h1 id="new-website"&gt;New Website&lt;a class="td-heading-self-link" href="#new-website" aria-label="Heading self-link"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;With my previous website, I put it together with Wordpress. As what typically happens, WordPress was just too cumbersome for me to maintain. Additionally, it seemed like someone was always trying to hack it. It was a pain and I worried about the hacks.&lt;/p&gt;
